        "title": "agent.py",
        "content": "\n**Gaps:** `cmd_db_new`'s posted-date filtering (dropped/kept/undated counters) and its group-boundary truncation logic are the most intricate untested code outside `fetchers.py` — a truncation bug here would silently split a batch's history mid-group. `_normalize_ats`'s tag-boundary-respecting substitution is also unverified (a regression could corrupt HTML tags/CSS while \"fixing\" smart quotes).\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 2
